For sale is an immaculate manufactured in 1954 High Standard Dura-Matic .22 lr semi-auto pistol. This gun is in “as-new” condition both functionally and cosmetically. Bluing pristine, without marks, and grips/handles are in absolutely perfect condition with no wear visible. 

This model has “threaded” barrel-removal system (see picture), which is superior to the “push-button” models because it does NOT have any springs to wear out over time and it functions as well after 1,000 take downs as it does when new. It also has a locking side button on the thumbwheel that keeps the threaded retention wheel absolutely tight while shooting. 

It has the famous High Standard “loaded chamber” indicator on the rear of the slide. The safety on the rear of the frame also functions as the slide lock. Mag release is located left forward, above the trigger guard. Handles both standard and high-velocity .22 lr ammo. Not recommended for hyper-velocity rounds, such as Stingers. People shoot 'em in HS pistols, but I've never fired any in THIS weapon.

This gun is SOLID metal. It is pure joy to hold, shoot, and handle.

Firearm has no visible nicks, scratches, rust or other signs of wear inside or out. 

Two genuine High Standard magazine are included (one blued and one stainless), and both have been “tuned” to accept either CCI or Federal ammo (does not care for Remington cartridges, however).

I will include the carbon-steel magazine adjustment tool along with instructions so that the new owner may custom “fine tune” the mags for any desired ammo.

This firearm has absolutely NO issues.   Everything about this gun, inside and out, is 100%. The trigger pull is smooth and crisp, and sights are “on the money” for 25 – 50 yards.

Auction includes firearm, 2 magazines, speed loader, mag adjustment tool and padded gun case.

I also have the Owner's manual in electronic form, which I will email the buyer.

As a High Standard in this condition with 2 factory magazines is almost impossible to find, I'd like to  entertain serious cash offers in the $550 range. I would also consider partial trade for ammo.

.22 lr ammo, 9mm ammo, .380 auto ammo or 7.62x39 ammo
